        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 3:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ellicott, or 27 miles east of Colorado Springs, moving east at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Yoder, Truckton, Ellicott, and Rush.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
